icies\n* **Subscriptions:** Revenue from premium subscriptions on Grok is recognized **ratably over the subscription term**, which ranges from month-to-month up to one year.\n* **API Access:** Revenue from providing API access to Grok models is recognized ratably over the contract term (typically month-to-month or up to one year) for stand-ready access, or as services are consumed for usage-based arrangements.\n\n### 5. Future Monetization Opportunities\n* **Advertising Integration:** While Grok currently supports X\'s advertising strategy (helping with campaign creation and creative optimization), the company noted that it is still early in increasing paid penetration across the Grok user base. Management explicitly stated: *"We further believe there might be an incremental monetization opportunity by introducing advertising into our stand-alone Grok offering."*\n* **Enterprise & API:** Grok is also monetized via tailored enterprise deployments (*Grok Business and Grok Enterprise*) sold on license-, consumption-, or outcome-based pricing models, as well as through third-party compute and API agreements.',
