e MD&A\'s accounting policies explicitly list **API access to Grok models** as a core pillar of AI solutions and infrastructure revenue (noting it is recognized ratably over the contract term or as services are consumed for usage-based arrangements), the **Results of Operations narrative does not separately break out the specific dollar impact of API access growth** for any of the periods. Its financial impact is embedded in the slight variances between the total AI infrastructure revenue growth and the sum of the explicitly listed subscription and data licensing growth.',
